snippet.textDisplay: I bought a 3600 in early April.  Updated BIOS on mainboard, built PC, everything great.  I updated BIOS a week ago or so, and my CPU is running faster now.  MSI Dragon Center monitor used to pretty consistently show the CPU running at expected 3600 MHz but after update same machine in same config now running at 4200 MHz.  I had it in "Balanced" mode initially pre and post update.  I tried running in Silent mode and same results.  The updated MSI Bios seems to have dialed the CPU up to faster speeds.  Waddup with that?
snippet.textOriginal: I bought a 3600 in early April.  Updated BIOS on mainboard, built PC, everything great.  I updated BIOS a week ago or so, and my CPU is running faster now. I had it in "Balanced" mode initially pre and post update.  I tried running in Silent mode and same results.  The updated MSI Bios seems to have dialed the CPU up to faster speeds.  Waddup with that?
